Colombia’s Echeverry Was ‘Disappointed’ by ‘Opaque’ World Bank, IMF Talks

-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 
2011-09-29T12:04:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/colombia-s-echeverry-was-disappointed-by-opaque-world-bank-imf-talks.html
Colombian Finance Minister Juan
Carlos Echeverry said he came away “disappointed” from
meetings with the International Monetary Fund and  World Bank  in
 Washington  last week.  The message from the meetings was unclear and “opaque,”
Echeverry said during an Economist conference in  London  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Price in London at 
 lprice3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Karen Eeuwens at 
 keeuwens@bloomberg.net  